# Files Vercel CLI must NOT upload. Without this, `vercel deploy` from
# the repo root tries to push the whole monorepo plus every git worktree
# under .claude/worktrees/ (>4 GB), which aborts mid-upload.
#
# The Vercel project's Root Directory setting is `app/`, so we only need
# to upload that subtree. Everything else here is excluded.
#
# CRITICAL: leading slashes anchor each pattern to the repo root.
# Without them, `api` would (via gitignore semantics) also match
# `app/src/app/api/` and silently strip every Next.js API route from
# the upload — which is exactly the bug this comment exists to prevent.

# Sibling services + tooling not used by the Next.js app build.
/api
/docs
/tools
/skills
/Tabsignal

# Claude Code harness directory — includes worktrees with their own
# copies of node_modules. Huge and never needed for a build.
/.claude

# Build / install artifacts (defensive — should already be in .gitignore
# but Vercel reads its own ignore independently). These ARE safe to
# leave unanchored because Vercel doesn't have a legitimate
# `node_modules/` / `.next/` inside the upload tree.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/.cache
**/.DS_Store
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Local env files. Vercel injects env from project settings at build time.
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env*.local

# Backup / editor cruft
**/*.swp
**/*~
